{"type":"message","id":"fd4e93c7","parentId":"b7078652","timestamp":"2026-03-02T15:50:08.333Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there's a domains directory with just a template. Let me understand what the user is asking for. They're describing a system design for an orchestrator that:\n\n1. Runs every 15 minutes via cron\n2. Round-robins through channels\n3. Active hours: strategic questions, gap-filling, status checks\n4. Off hours: organizing, experiments, pattern analysis\n\nThis sounds like they want me to either:\n- Understand this design for future implementation\n- Help implement this system\n- Document this design\n\nGiven they said \"So the purpose is...\" they're likely explaining the design intent. I should acknowledge understanding and capture this in my memory, then ask what they'd like me to do with this information.\n\nLet me document this in today's memory file and clarify next steps.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. So the orchestrator is a **pulse-based channel nudge system**:\n\n| Phase | Behavior |\n|-------|----------|\n| **Active hours** | Conversational — one strategic question per channel per pulse, filling gaps, checking status |\n| **Off hours** | Reflective — organize artifacts, run experiments, analyze patterns (daily/weekly) |\n\n**Round-robin** = one channel per 15-min tick, not all channels every tick. Keeps it lightweight and spreads attention.\n\nA few clarifying questions:\n\n1. **Active hours definition** — What's the window? (e.g., 09:00–21:00 IST? Or per-channel preferences?)\n\n2. **Channel selection** — Round-robin across *all* Discord channels, or only ones with active/pending conversations?\n\n3. **\"Strategic questions\" scope** — Is this reading each channel's `purpose.md` + recent messages and deciding what to ask? Or more structured (e.g., pre-defined question templates)?\n\n4. **Where should this live?** — A skill? A cron-configured orchestrator script? Something the heartbeat system triggers?\n\nI'll capture the core design in memory once we lock in the details."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":268,"output":413,"cacheRead":14208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14889,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772466590692}}
{"type":"message","id":"623689c9","parentId":"fd4e93c7","timestamp":"2026-03-02T15:53:15.221Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-02 15:53 UTC] So the quiet hours is midnight India time to 5 a.m. India time, and everything else after that is considered active hours . So the channel selection is round robin across all Discord channels with no exception Yes, it has to read the channel's purpose and recent messages, and all the everything it has access to that's related to that particular channel. So it shouldn't read the content for other channels, but it should read system-wide messages and it should read the previous logs of what it did previously, just so that it doesn't keep repeating the same thing. Basically, it should come up with a single question to move the channel's conversation one step closer to its purpose. This could be like filling in gaps or asking questions about a particular project, any of these types of things . Look for a file, I think there is a policy.md file somewhere. All of this should go there in that file, all of these instructions should go there"}],"timestamp":1772466795219}}
{"type":"message","id":"2bc763bb","parentId":"623689c9","timestamp":"2026-03-02T15:53:18.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to find a policy.md file where these orchestrator instructions should go. Let me search for it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_38b68f3fc2be4efba85274fb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /root/.openclaw/workspace -name \"policy.md\" -o -name \"POLICY.md\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":967,"output":62,"cacheRead":13760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14789,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772466795221}}
